snippet.textDisplay: I did something worse to my friend back in the 70’s. Lynn was an singer. She had very dark brown hair down to her waist. Lynn, is 5’8”. She wanted her long hair frosted. Highlighting hadn’t been invented yet😳I had done everything to my hair, so I thought I knew enough. I watched my other friend, Tina, do hair for years in her salon. I used an old fashioned rubber frosting cap. I did buy the bleach from the salon. I pulled her 4’ long pieces of hair out if the cap, applied the bleach and waited. I think we left it on for an hour. It turned a very nice blond. S few weeks later, Lynn had to cut her hair off. It was so damaged she couldn’t brush it. Lynn used to do a perfect Cher with her long hair. I felt horrible for destroyed her thick, thick, long beautiful hair. We are still friends going on 55 years. Lynn has never worn her hair long since the incident💕💕💕💕💕

snippet.textDisplay: i feel bad for her but as someone who’s been bleaching and colouring and cutting my own hair since i was 12 years old i only feel bad to a certain point- what was she expecting when she clearly didn’t do any sort of research whatsoever?? and also she could’ve easily told her friends to stop- like my best friend who’s literally in hairdressing school is just as ignorant as her friends so i had to tell him to stop touching my hair bc i knew he was going to fuck it up. i didn’t care if i hurt his feelings. it’s my hair. like she could’ve easily avoided that whole situation if she went onto youtube for 5 minutes to search for a hairdressers channel. like yes maybe i have an advantage bc my grandfather is a hairdresser so my mother grew up in a salon and has experience with this but she never really taught me how to do it. it was me researching things and learning how my own hair works. i’m lucky enough to have hair that apparently never wants to die (i’ve used a stripper and bleached it twice and dyed it all in the same night and it didn’t get damaged at ALL) but still. i know how asian hair bleaches, i’ve done my friends hair before. it’s not difficult if you do it right. as brad said, yes it only gets so light. but it’s so EASY to get it to a beautiful lightness without it falling off.

snippet.textDisplay:
While in high school I had my hair frosted and all the blond fell out, it wasn't a big deal cause I had a lot of hair and you couldn't tell because the blond was such a small amount...….2 girls with their entire head bleached tried to do a retouch which was overlapped, all their hair broke off except the roots and they wore wigs to prom. The first of these scenarios was because my (virgin) hair was not strong enough for the professional strength bleach. The second was because these girls were vain and the tiniest amount of regrowth was too much.
You can't understand why she is smiling, would tears bring her hair back, one nice thing about hair it grows back.
